OL,3,CRelief for Channel Island athletes as
OL,4,C2026 Commonwealths confirmed for
OL,5,CGlasgow
OL,7,F56 Channel Islanders competed at the
OL,8,F2022 Games in Birmingham which saw
OL,9,FGuernsey win their first medal in 28
OL,10,Fyears when Lawn bowler Lucy Beere won
OL,11,Fsilver.
OL,13,FGlasgow hosted the 2014 Games which
OL,14,Ffeatured 18 sports.
OL,16,FHowever, there will only be 10 sports
OL,17,Fin the scaled-back 2026 Commonwealths
OL,18,Fwith only athletics and swimming
OL,19,Fconfirmed so far.
